---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="How to Use This Portfolio Manager — Global Wealth Portfolio Blog"
  description="A complete walkthrough of Global Wealth Portfolio — from importing your first investment to tracking expenses, setting goals, and monitoring benchmarks."
>
  <article class="container-page page-section pt-3xl pb-2xl max-w-3xl">
    <a href="/blog" class="inline-flex items-center gap-xs text-body-sm text-link hover:underline mb-md">&larr; Back to blog</a>
    <p class="text-caption-mono text-gold mb-xs">Blog</p>
    <h1 class="text-display-lg mb-md">How to Use This Portfolio Manager</h1>
    <p class="text-caption text-mute mb-lg">June 9, 2026 · 6 min read</p>

    <div class="prose-custom text-body-md text-body leading-relaxed space-y-md">
      <p>
        Global Wealth Portfolio is designed to be intuitive, but a guided walkthrough helps
        you get the most out of it from day one. Whether you are migrating from a spreadsheet
        or starting fresh, this guide covers every feature you need to take control of your
        financial life.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink mt-3xl mb-md">Step 1: Add your investments</h2>
      <p>
        The fastest way to get started is to import a spreadsheet. Head to the
        <a href="/import" class="text-link hover:underline">Import page</a> and drop an Excel
        or CSV file from your broker, bank, or your own tracking sheet. Global Wealth Portfolio
        automatically detects columns for asset name, type, amount, date, and more. Multi-sheet
        workbooks are fully supported — a single file with separate tabs for investments,
        expenses, and loans gets routed to the right place automatically.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you prefer to add entries one at a time, the
        <a href="/investments" class="text-link hover:underline">Investments page</a> lets you
        manually log each holding. Choose the asset type (equity, debt, gold, crypto, real estate,
        or custom), enter the amount in your preferred currency, and tag it with a date and notes.
        Every entry updates your portfolio in real time.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink mt-3xl mb-md">Step 2: Track your expenses</h2>
      <p>
        Go to the <a href="/expenses" class="text-link hover:underline">Expenses page</a> to
        log your monthly spending. You can enter expenses manually or upload a bank statement
        image — the on-device OCR reads the text, extracts transactions, and suggests categories.
        Nothing is ever uploaded to a server.
      </p>
      <p>
        Categories help you understand where your money goes. Tag expenses as food, transport,
        utilities, entertainment, or create custom categories. The dashboard then shows you
        spending breakdowns by category and month, so you can identify patterns and adjust your
        budget.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink mt-3xl mb-md">Step 3: Set financial goals</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="/goals" class="text-link hover:underline">Goals page</a> is where you plan
        for the future. Create a goal for retirement, a home purchase, an education fund, or
        any target. Set the target amount, target date, and expected annual return. The platform
        projects your corpus forward under conservative, expected, and optimistic scenarios —
        all adjusted for inflation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each goal shows a progress bar, the amount saved so far, and the monthly contribution
        needed to stay on track. You can link specific investments or a monthly SIP to a goal,
        making it easy to see how each contribution brings you closer.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink mt-3xl mb-md">Step 4: Monitor benchmarks</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="/benchmarks" class="text-link hover:underline">Benchmarks page</a> compares
        your portfolio return against major indices — NIFTY 50, S&amp;P 500, Gold, Silver, and
        several sectoral indices. This helps you evaluate whether your active investment choices
        are outperforming or underperforming the market, and make data-driven rebalancing decisions.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink mt-3xl mb-md">Step 5: Review the dashboard</h2>
      <p>
        The <a href="/dashboard" class="text-link hover:underline">Dashboard</a> is your
        command centre. It shows your net worth, asset allocation, recent transactions,
        goal progress, and expense trends — all in one scrollable view. Every number updates
        as you add data, giving you a real-time picture of your financial health.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-display-md text-ink mt-3xl mb-md">Pro tips</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-lg space-y-xs">
        <li><strong>Export regularly.</strong> Use the Settings page to export your portfolio as JSON or CSV. This is your backup.</li>
        <li><strong>Use the EMI tracker.</strong> Log your loans on the EMI page to see how they affect your net worth and monthly cash flow.</li>
        <li><strong>Check the audit trail.</strong> Every change is recorded. The Audit page gives you a complete history of additions, edits, and deletions.</li>
        <li><strong>Customise your currency and language.</strong> Use the controls in the top navigation to switch between 30+ currencies and 10+ languages.</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-3xl">
        That is all there is to it. Start by
        <a href="/import" class="text-link hover:underline">importing your data</a> or
        <a href="/dashboard" class="text-link hover:underline">opening the dashboard</a>.
        Your financial life, organised and private — all in your browser.
      </p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
